Edition:
Quote: We observ'd already that the principal fish caught by the seyne were Mullets [ed. fn <i>Aldrichetta forsteri </i>.] and Elephant fish [ed. fn <i>Callarhyncus milli </i>.] & a few soles [ed. fn <i>Peltorhamphus novaeseelandiae </i>.] and flounders, [ed. fn <i>Rhombosalea </i> spp.] but those which the Indians mostly supply'd us with are a sort of sea Bream of a silver colour with a black spot on the neck, [ed. fn Tarakihi, ...] ...
